task.summary: Corrected get_DAP_deflection: now gives the absolute value Updated example wit units
Uses now matplotlib FigureCanvas and NavigationToolbar for plots
Variables are now initialized to their lower bound
Added FitterFactory and Fitter now have to know their name, Update evaluation scripts (fIcurve, hyperdap, phaseplot) correspondingly
Added FitterFactory and Fitter now have to know their name, Update evaluate as well
Fixed observer problem for inspyred optimizer with multiprocessing
Functions to plot vclamp steps of ion channel and activation curves, time constant curves
Changed scipy multiprocessing to only start as many processes as there are cores
Added climin optimizer and fixed multiprocessing bug in scipy_optimizer Processes did not stop because working_queue.get() never returned None, now it checks for working_queue.empty()
Added look_for_good_cells that goes through the data set and returns the cells with good characteristics
Added visualizations of experimental channels (activation function, time constants, etc.)
plot PP for different steps and amplitudes
made hyperdap.py conform to the experiments
added save_PP.py for saving all PP files and rampIV for plotting reponse for different amplitudes
updated evaluate methods, to make cell from model_dir instead of searching through optimization results
DAP_population: package for finding spikes in rampIV and later investigating DAPs
new scripts for fitting different cells
added package for analysis of grid cell stimuli
added saving of params, runs and evaluation of those
added simulation of speed and position and computation of firing fields based on field positions
plot comparing patch, sharp recording in vivo and vitro when pos. current step is applied
